    "description": "Ebstein's Anomaly is a congenital heart defect characterized by an abnormality of the tricuspid valve and the right side of the heart. In this condition, the tricuspid valve is malformed and positioned lower than normal in the right ventricle, which can lead to dysfunctional blood flow and decreased efficiency of the heart. This anomaly can result in various complications, including heart enlargement, arrhythmias, and heart failure. Symptoms often vary in severity depending on the extent of the defect and associated conditions.",
    "symptoms": [
